mh_accident_explain: My pain started with an accident in Oct 2013. I was on a motorcycle and someone ran into me with their car, which broke my left femur, and my face bones, and tore cartilage and tendons in my ankles and knees. The surgeon who implanted the intermedullary rod placed it wrong, and then refused to admit his mistake. I suffered for 4 years with that rod pressing on my bone , the pain was unimaginable. Doctors in GA all refused to take it out. They also refused to fix any of the other damage from the accident and told me I was just making up all these things. So I suffered for years. Finally in 2017 the 5th surgeon I spoke to begrudgingly took the rod out. It was too late though. The pain was burned into my nerve. So now I have something called central sensitization and I still have about 75% of the pain of the rod pressing on my bone even though its gone. Now, 8 years after the accident, I live in UT and I am finally able to get some medical treatments and surgeries for all these things they left uncorrected in GA, but I will probably have chronic pain for rest of my life because of the negligence and discrimination of the doctors back in GA
mh_pain_cause: Mostly my pain was caused by discrimination and medical neglect.
